JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa has apologised to Mama Winnie Madikizela-Mandela for her not having been awarded the Isithwalandwe honour. Isithwalandwe is the highest honour awarded to South Africans for their outstanding contribution and sacrifice to the liberation struggle. MT: #WinnieMandela #WinnieMadikizelaMandela #WinnieMandelaFuneral Ramaphosa said on an organisational note, he'll propose to the NEC that Madikizela-Mandela be bestowed Isithwalandwe Seaparankoe, the ANC's highest honour to those who made outstanding contributions to the struggle "I'm sorry mama that your organisation delayed you in according you its honour. I'll propose that you be bestowed the highest honour of Seaparankwe Isithwalandwe," said Ramaphosa. eNCA